<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-445-740  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 445 740.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 14 1990 n367 p45(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Global sales growth slows. (computer industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Revenue growth for computer manufacturers is slowing domesticallyand abroad, but international sales overall increased to 50.1percent of revenue in 1989.andP;  In 1988, overseas sales accounted for48.4 percent of computer manufacturers' worldwide business.andP;  Thosesurveyed include Compaq and IBM, which both have internationalsales that account for more than 50 percent of their totalbusiness.andP;  Despite the growth, the international market isexpected to slow, especially in Europe.andP;  Europe will stillgenerate more revenue for the leading vendors than the US market,however.andP;  The Asia/Pacific region is also seeing a slowdown inrevenue growth, from 25.1 percent in 1988 to 12.7 percent in 1989.andO;The Gartner Group Inc survey is based on a five-year market andfinancial analysis of the top 100 US computer vendors.andP;  Factorsinclude revenue growth, research and development, capitalexpenditures and operating income.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gartner Group Inc. (surveys).andO;Topic:     Industry AnalysisInternational TradeGrowthComputer IndustrySurvey.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   International growth. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>